6. Create sublists for participants with functional and anatomical data
bash /Raid/Current/Miray/MRI/codes/codes/cleaning_and_bidsifying/create_func_and_nofunc_sublists

This script scans a BIDS output directory for participant folders (named sub-*) and sorts them into three text lists:
     1. sublist_all.txt      — every participant found
     2. sublist_func.txt     — participants who HAVE a func/ folder
     3. sublist_no_func.txt  — participants who DO NOT have a func/ folder

1. Creates the three list files at the start of each run.
2. Loops over every folder in BIDS_OUTPUT whose name starts with "sub-".
3. For each participant folder:
     a. Strips the "sub-" prefix to get the clean participant ID (e.g. "sub-FAAH001" → "FAAH001").
     b. Adds the clean ID to the ALL list.
     c. Checks whether a "func" subfolder exists anywhere inside the participant folder.
     d. Adds the ID to either the FUNC or NO_FUNC list accordingly.
