7. Uploading data to SCC
Once all your mri data is bidsified, it's time to run fmriprep. 
It's better to run it on a cluster (you can run it locally, but this will take much longer)
A cluster that I like to use is the SCC. Fist you have to set up an SCC account, once you do that you're ready to get started!

First you have to upload three folders from your local computer unto the SCC
BIDS_OUTPUT: this is the path to your bids
fmriprep codes: /Raid/Current/Miray/MRI/codes/codes/fmriprep_code (you only have to upload this once for all your studies)
templates:/Raid/Current/Miray/MRI/templates (you only have to upload this once for all your studies)

To upload folders to SCC, you have to open a new terminal (do not log into SCC!) and type command: 
scp -v -r /path/to/folder/you/wanna/move scc_username@local_computer_ip_address:/output/path/in/scc

Then, on the SCC create 2 new folders
mkdir work (clean this after each fmriprep job finishes running)
mkdir temp (clean this after each fmriprep job finishes running)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8. Running fmriprep on SCC
Once your BIDS_OUPUT folder and everything else is uploaded, you can run two fmriprep codes:
sbatch /path/to/fmriprep_code/run_fmriprep_curb_anat.sh
sbatch /path/to/fmriprep_code/run_fmriprep_curb_func.sh

This will create two "jobs" for the cluster and will give you a job ID for each one.
You can check on their progress by typing "squeue jobID"
Participants that successfully ran will have .htmls in the fmriprep_outputs folder

Congratulations! You just ran fmriprep!
